article.headline: Delaware St. 72, Norfolk St. 61
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Roy Bright scored 18 points and Aaron Fleetwood and Jahsha Bluntt each added 17 to lead Delaware State to a 72-61 win over Norfolk State on Monday night. Norfolk led 35-29 at the half, but a 3-pointer by Bluntt with 12:48 left in the game put the Hornets (16-12, 14-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) ahead for good. Tony Murphy led the Spartans (8-16, 8-6) with 12 points, and Calvin Brown added 11. Delaware outshot Norfolk 55.6 percent to 49 percent from the field. Norfolk outrebounded Delaware 26-24.
